The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the NASA Ames Research Center in Silicon Valley. He expressed his condolences for the shooting at Saugus High School in Santa Clarita and promised support from the federal government. Pence praised NASA Ames for its contributions to American leadership in space and highlighted the role it will play in future space exploration. He mentioned the goal of returning American astronauts to the Moon within the next five years and emphasized the importance of public-private partnerships in the space industry. Pence also commended the work being done at NASA Ames in developing new technologies and innovations for space exploration. He concluded his speech by expressing confidence in the future of American space exploration and the men and women involved in the endeavor.